<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Cue" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Cue,</orth> the catch-word: <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.3.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 3, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.316" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 316</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 1, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 1, 78</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.205" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 205</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.186.205" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 186</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.4.27" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 4, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.147" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 147</bibl>. Hence == sign, hint, motive: <cit><quote>the clock gives me my c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 2, 46</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>now we speak upon our c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.130" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 130</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>what would he do, had he the motive and the c. for passion that I have?</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.587" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 587</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>were it my c. to fight,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.2.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 2, 83</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>